2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper tests the robustness of the proposed methods on real data extracted from a corpus of text documents. This indicates that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computation and language.
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions problems involving dimensionality reduction, which is a common problem in computer vision. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes algorithms for learning with clustering penalties, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper mentions the core iteration complexity of the proposed algorithms, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms.
